<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFCC3354FF52F9937191F89C" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCC3355FF52F9937066F954" blockId="20.[166,1225,1617,1868]" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCC3355FE0BF99073C4F9F3" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[386,503,1617,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FE0BF99073A6F9F4" box="[386,405,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FE28F99373C4F9F3" box="[417,503,1617,1643]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs in a group of species characterized by the partly black head, thorax, and usually also abdomen or legs, dark patterned wing (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FC57F9B37619F914" box="[990,1066,1649,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[173,206,1466,1488]" captionTargetBox="[201,1225,188,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-121@21.[174,1233,171,1452]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 23. Campylocera laticeps: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — vein R4+5 (arrow indicates setula); 4 — head, left; 5 — same, anterior; 6 — same, dorsal; 7 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 8 — fore femur and tibia, posterior; 9 — mid leg, anterior; 10 — hind leg, anterior view; 11 — male genitalia, ventral view; 12 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453753/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">fig. 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FBBFF9B37677F913" box="[1078,1092,1649,1675]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,680,702]" captionTargetBox="[280,1119,174,659]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[272,1122,174,674]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Campylocera ferruginea, holotype (MHNP): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 4 — head, anterior view; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453688/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FBBFF9B37677F913" box="[1078,1092,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FBDBF9B37643F914" box="[1106,1136,1649,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[166,199,531,553]" captionTargetBox="[212,1175,191,485]" captionTargetId="figure-456@22.[163,1220,174,503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 24. Campylocera similis: paratypes ♀ (1–2) and Ơ (3) (MRAC): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — male genitalia, ventral view (slide)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453755/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FBF4F9B376B8F913" box="[1149,1163,1649,1675]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1748,1770]" captionTargetBox="[272,1113,774,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-10@3.[272,1122,774,1719]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Campylocera ferruginea: holotype ♀ of Campylocera omissa (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 3 — head, anterior view; 4 —wing; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior view (arrow indicates long setae); 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior view; 9–10 — oviscape, dorsal and left view; 11 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453690/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FBF4F9B376B8F913" box="[1149,1163,1649,1675]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) and more or less conspicuously developed ocellar triangle with 2–4 ocellar setae and antenna with long pedicel and flagellomere 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCC3354FF52F9137191F89C" blockId="20.[166,1225,1617,1868]" lastBlockId="21.[174,1233,1609,1860]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
Within this group, about six described and undescribed species differing by the very high gena (0.5–0.7× as high as eye), large shining brown ocellar triangle 0.3–0.5 as long as frons width (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FEB4F8D373B4F8B4" box="[317,391,1809,1836]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[173,206,1466,1488]" captionTargetBox="[201,1225,188,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-121@21.[174,1233,171,1452]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 23. Campylocera laticeps: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — vein R4+5 (arrow indicates setula); 4 — head, left; 5 — same, anterior; 6 — same, dorsal; 7 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 8 — fore femur and tibia, posterior; 9 — mid leg, anterior; 10 — hind leg, anterior view; 11 — male genitalia, ventral view; 12 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453753/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">fig. 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FE1AF8D37392F8B3" box="[403,417,1809,1835]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,206,1007,1029]" captionTargetBox="[262,1101,174,970]" captionTargetId="figure-6@7.[262,1119,174,1000]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.6. Campylocera kiwuensis holotype Ơ (MRAC):1 — habitus, lateral view;2 — wing; 3 — head,right; 4 — head, dorsal view; 5 — palp; 6 — fore leg, posterior view; 7 — hind leg, anterior view; 8 — epandrium, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453704/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FE1AF8D37392F8B3" box="[403,417,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">6</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), non-spinulose mid and hind coxae (in both sexes), very large, nonseparated cerci and extremely narrow medial surstylus (in male — as on 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FC63F8F37601F8D4" box="[1002,1074,1841,1868]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[166,199,531,553]" captionTargetBox="[212,1175,191,485]" captionTargetId="figure-456@22.[163,1220,174,503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 24. Campylocera similis: paratypes ♀ (1–2) and Ơ (3) (MRAC): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — male genitalia, ventral view (slide)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453755/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">fig. 24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCC3355FBB5F8F37679F8D3" box="[1084,1098,1841,1867]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[168,201,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[292,1119,675,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-200@4.[272,1119,667,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Campylocera ferruginea, non-type Ơ (1–6) and ♀ (7–11) (Nigeria, USNM): 1–2 — genitalia, right and ventral view; 3 — outer and inner surstyli, ventral view; 4–6 — phallus glans at different angles; 7 — oviscape apex; 8 — aculeus; 9 — vagina and ventral receptacle; 10 — medioventral lobe; 11 — spermathecae (2 of 3)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453694/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCC3355FBB5F8F37679F8D3" box="[1084,1098,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="215">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) and short (as long as abdominal tergites combined), wide conical oviscape (as on 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCD3354FB89F98B7679F9FC" box="[1024,1098,1609,1636]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[166,199,531,553]" captionTargetBox="[212,1175,191,485]" captionTargetId="figure-456@22.[163,1220,174,503]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 24. Campylocera similis: paratypes ♀ (1–2) and Ơ (3) (MRAC): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — male genitalia, ventral view (slide)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453755" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453755/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">fig. 24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFCD3354FBDEF98B7656F9FB" box="[1111,1125,1609,1635]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,680,702]" captionTargetBox="[280,1119,174,659]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[272,1122,174,674]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Campylocera ferruginea, holotype (MHNP): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 — wing; 3 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 4 — head, anterior view; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453688/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FBDEF98B7656F9FB" box="[1111,1125,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) bearing around apical aperture one moderately long dorsomedial lobe, paired sensillar brushes (rows of 3–4 closely located thick setulae) and short latero-ventral lobes form a subgroup that corresponds to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCD3354FD95F9687099F95B" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[540,682,1706,1731]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FD95F9687099F95B" box="[540,682,1706,1731]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">Diasteneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the species differ mostly by the coloration of body and wings, and vestiture of scutellum and legs. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCD3354FC9FF90871B8F97B" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[790,907,1737,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FC9FF908711AF97C" box="[790,809,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FCBCF90B71B8F97B" box="[821,907,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from them all by the occiput entirely yellow (partly or entirely black in other species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="0A950EFFFFCD3354FF24FA78736AF9B8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453753" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453753/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" startId="21.[173,206,1466,1488]" targetBox="[201,1225,188,1435]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCD3354FF24FA78736AF9B8" blockId="21.[173,1232,1464,1568]" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">
Fig. 23. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCD3354FF71FA7873F2FA57" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[248,449,1466,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FF71FA7873F2FA57" box="[248,449,1466,1487]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">Campylocera laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: holotype ♀ (NHMW): 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FD21FA787080FA57" box="[680,691,1466,1487]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">1</emphasis>
— habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FC29FA787198FA57" box="[928,939,1466,1487]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">2</emphasis>
— wing; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FB81FA787620FA57" box="[1032,1043,1466,1487]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">3</emphasis>
— vein R 
<subScript id="C26E5C32FFCD3354FBFDFA0B76BAFA4E" attach="left" box="[1140,1161,1481,1494]" fontSize="5" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">4+5</subScript>
(arrow indicates setula); 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FEDCFA177353FA72" box="[341,352,1493,1514]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">4</emphasis>
— head, left; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FE6CFA1773C3FA72" box="[485,496,1493,1514]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">5</emphasis>
— same, anterior; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FD2EFA167081FA71" box="[679,690,1492,1513]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">6</emphasis>
— same, dorsal; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FCD1FA177150FA72" box="[856,867,1493,1514]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">7</emphasis>
— mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FBF4FA1776BBFA72" box="[1149,1160,1493,1514]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">8</emphasis>
— fore femur and tibia, posterior; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FE3EFA2D73F1F99C" box="[439,450,1519,1540]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">9</emphasis>
— mid leg, anterior; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FD11FA2D709CF99C" box="[664,687,1519,1540]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">10</emphasis>
— hind leg, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FC34FA2D71E7F99C" box="[957,980,1519,1540]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">11</emphasis>
— male genitalia, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FF6CF9C872CFF987" box="[229,252,1546,1567]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">12</emphasis>
— labels.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFCD3357FF6AF8CB7607FC10" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="217" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFCD3357FF6AF8CB7607FC10" blockId="21.[174,1233,1609,1860]" lastBlockId="22.[166,1225,621,904]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="217" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">
R e m a r k. Species assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCD3354FDCBF8C870E3F8BB" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[578,720,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCD3354FDCBF8C870E3F8BB" box="[578,720,1802,1827]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="216">Diasteneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form a well-defined, certainly monophyletic group supported at least by such synapomomorphies as high gena and large ocellar triangle, and possibly some sexually dimorphic characters, which are known only for some species of this subgroup (only one species is known from both species by far). None of the characters contradict their placement into 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCE3357FDA9FD6F708BFD5F" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[544,696,685,711]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FDA9FD6F708BFD5F" box="[544,696,685,711]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and I therefore synonymize the latter name and 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCE3357FF54FD0C7027FD70" authority="Hendel, 1908" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[221,532,717,744]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FF54FD0C7358FD7F" box="[221,363,718,743]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Diasteneura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFCE3357FEFCFD0F7027FD70" author="Hendel, F." box="[373,532,717,744]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref11436" refString="Hendel, F. 1908. Acht neue Pyrgotinen (Dipt.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 27 (4 - 5), 145 - 153." type="journal article" year="1908">Hendel, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FD97FD0F7074FD7F" bold="true" box="[542,583,717,743]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">syn</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FDD1FD0F705AFD7F" bold="true" box="[600,617,717,743]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">n</emphasis>
. The species formerly assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCE3357FB85FD0C76A9FD7F" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[1036,1178,718,743]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Diasteneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FB85FD0C76A9FD7F" box="[1036,1178,718,743]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Diasteneura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are transferred: 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCE3357FEB5FD2F71ADFC90" authority="(Vanschuytbroeck, 1963)" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Vanschuytbroeck" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[316,926,749,776]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basilewskyi" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FEB5FD2F7051FC9F" box="[316,610,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Campylocera basilewskyi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFCE3357FDFFFD2F71A5FC90" author="Vanschuytbroeck, P." box="[630,918,749,776]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref12157" refString="Vanschuytbroeck, P. 1963. Pyrgotidae (Diptera Otitoidea). Institut des Parcs Nationaux du Congo et du Rwanda, Exploration du Parc National de la Garamba, Miss. H. De Saeger, 38, 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1963">Vanschuytbroeck, 1963</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="77AD3F1EFFCE3357FC26FD2F762EFC90" box="[943,1053,749,776]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" rank="species">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FC26FD2F71C0FC9F" bold="true" box="[943,1011,749,775]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">comb</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FB8FFD2F7624FC9F" bold="true" box="[1030,1047,749,775]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFCE3357FBB9FD2F73FDFCB0" authority="(Hendel, 1908)" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFCE3357FBB9FD2F72CFFCBF" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Campylocera laticeps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3A7B2386FFCE3357FE9EFCCF73F6FCB0" author="Hendel, F." box="[279,453,781,808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref11436" refString="Hendel, F. 1908. Acht neue Pyrgotinen (Dipt.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 27 (4 - 5), 145 - 153." type="journal article" year="1908">Hendel, 1908</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="77AD3F1EFFCE3357FE6FFCCF7069FCB0" box="[486,602,781,808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" rank="species">
